messages.content: What is the purpose of ComfyUI-Image-Browsing?
ComfyUI-Image-Browsing is a custom node for ComfyUI that allows users to browse and view images within the ComfyUI interface.
To install ComfyUI-Image-Browsing, navigate to the 'ComfyUI/custom_nodes' directory in the command line and run the command 'git clone https://github.com/hayden-fr/ComfyUI-Image-Browsing.git'.
In which directory should you install ComfyUI-Image-Browsing?
ComfyUI-Image-Browsing should be installed in the 'ComfyUI/custom_nodes' directory.
Is ComfyUI-Image-Browsing an official part of ComfyUI or a third-party extension?
ComfyUI-Image-Browsing is a third-party custom node that extends the functionality of ComfyUI.
From which source can you clone the ComfyUI-Image-Browsing repository?
You can clone the ComfyUI-Image-Browsing repository from 'https://github.com/hayden-fr/ComfyUI-Image-Browsing.git'.
Yes, ComfyUI-Image-Browsing is hosted on GitHub at 'https://github.com/hayden-fr/ComfyUI-Image-Browsing.git'.
Is ComfyUI-Image-Browsing a custom node or a plugin?
ComfyUI-Image-Browsing is a custom node for ComfyUI.
